Package org.parboiled.matchers

Interface Summary
Matcher<V> A Matcher instance is responsible for "executing" a specific Rule instance, i.e.
MatcherVisitor<V,R> The interface to be implemented by all visitors of Matchers.
 

Class Summary
AbstractMatcher<V> Abstract base class of most regular Matchers.
ActionMatcher<V> A Matcher that not actually matches input but runs a given parser Action.
CharactersMatcher<V> A Matcher matching a single character out of a given Characters set.
CharIgnoreCaseMatcher<V> A Matcher matching a single character case-independently.
CharMatcher<V> A Matcher matching a single given character.
CharRangeMatcher<V> A Matcher matching a single character out of a given range of characters.
EmptyMatcher<V> A Matcher that always successfully matches nothing.
FirstOfMatcher<V> A Matcher trying all of its submatchers in sequence and succeeding when the first submatcher succeeds.
OneOrMoreMatcher<V> A Matcher that repeatedly tries its sub matcher against the input.
OptionalMatcher<V> A Matcher that tries its sub matcher once against the input and always succeeds.
ProxyMatcher<V> A Matcher that delegates all Rule and Matcher interface methods to another Matcher.
SequenceMatcher<V> A Matcher that executes all of its sub matcher in sequence and only succeeds, if all sub matchers succeed.
TestMatcher<V> A special Matcher not actually matching any input but rather trying its sub matcher against the current input position.
TestNotMatcher<V> A special Matcher not actually matching any input but rather trying its sub matcher against the current input position.
ZeroOrMoreMatcher<V> A Matcher that repeatedly tries its sub matcher against the input.
